AMD has released a driver update for the X399 platform to support NVMe RAID. The driver is made for the Ryzen Threadripper platform on Windows 10 64-bit. “By combining multiple NVMe SSDs together into a RAID 0, 1, or 10 array, it is possible to greatly enhance disk performance or data integrity,” said AMD. With a single GPU in the system, arrays containing up to six NVMe SSDs can be supported without adapters. AMD said known issues with the driver were: